md:
giải nghĩa từ "impr" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan.
impr. ( abbreviation )
- impr. = imperative (from)
VD: The manager's instructions were imperative, and we had to follow them immediately.
- impr. = imperial (from)
VD: The imperial system of measurement is still used in some countries.
- impr. = impression (from)
VD: The first impression I got of the city was that it was very crowded.
- impr. = import (from)
VD: The company imports goods from several countries around the world.
- impr. = improvement (from)
VD: The new policy has led to a significant improvement in customer satisfaction.

Note: The abbreviation "impr." can have different meanings depending on the context in which it is used.
